{"quote": "One Hundred Years of Solitde", "page_title": "Love in the Time of Cholera", "page_bio": "Love in the Time of Cholera (El amor en los tiempos del c\u00f3lera, 1985) is a novel by Gabriel Garc\u00eda M\u00e1rquez about a fifty-year love triangle between Fermina Daza, Florentino Ariza and Doctor Juvenal Urbino set in the late 19th century and the first decades of the 20th century (roughly 1880 to 1930). The novel, a picturesque tale of unrequited love, which is written in M\u00e1rquezs trademark form of magical realism, deeply explores the idea that suffering for love is a kind of nobility.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Love in the Time of Cholera"}